{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "It achieves this by using cryptographic algorithms and decentralization to ensure that the data stored on the blockchain is immutable and transparent.",
    "In the context of IoT-based bio-and medical informatics, blockchain can be used to secure the data generated by IoT devices and ensure its integrity, authenticity, and privacy.",
    "For example, blockchain can be used to create a secure and tamper-proof log of all the data generated by IoT devices, which can be accessed only by authorized parties [145].",
    "Additionally, blockchain can implement secure and privacy-preserving data sharing mechanisms between healthcare providers and researchers.",
    "However, the use of blockchain in this context also comes with its own challenges and risks [146]."
  ],
